THE TENEDOS. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 7, 1907.) Nos. 110-114. Appeals from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Harrington Putnam, for appellants. Lawrence Kneeland, J. Tanner, and Black & Kneeland, for appellee.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and TOWNSEND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decrees of District Court (137 Fed. 443) affirmed, with interest and costs, upon opinion of Judge Holt.
